                        (?)</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>The owner (?) Walda Mikāʾel is mentioned in the
                     supplication formulas throughout the Ms., sometimes together with his wife
                     Walatta Gabrǝʾel (e.g., <locus target="#6va">6va</locus>), his father Tasfā
                     Māryām (e.g., <locus target="#7ra">7ra</locus>), his mother Walatta ʾAnanya
                     (e.g., <locus target="#7ra">7ra</locus>) and other relatives.
 The names of
                     other individuals are written (in rose ink) on <locus target="#40va">40va</locus> and 54vb: Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer and Walatta Śǝllāse on <locus target="#40va">40va</locus>; Walatta Māryām, Ḫāyla Māryām, Gabra Ḥawarya and
                     Gabra Māryām on <locus target="#54vb">54vb</locus>.</provenance>
               </history>
